  "body": "At initial downloading - we do `t.Drop()` for completed files, to improve performance. It reducing `total data size in logs` - it confusing users, because progress looks like: \r\n```\r\nprogress=\"11% 80Gb/600Gb\r\nprogress=\"14% 100Gb/700Gb\"\r\nprogress=\"13% 90Gb/690Gb\"\r\n```\r\nsometime goes down. \r\n\r\nNeed revisit: maybe we don't need \"drop to improve performance\" - maybe it was some bug in the past  (need test on big networks like Mainnet or BorMainnet)",
